Content-type: application/json  {
    "secret": "secret",
    "details": {
        "purpose": "Transportation ticket",
        "company": "Transdev",
        "seat": "A45",
        "destinations": "Aveiro",
        "price": 0
    }
}     Field  Description  Type      secret  Value to use when creating the hash  String    details  Aditional information about the ticket  Object

If successful, the response body contains a newly created instance of Ticket.  Content-type: application/json  {
    "ticket_id": 0,
    "timestamp": "2019-10-14T10:04:30.651Z",
    "details": {
        "purpose": "Transportation ticket",
        "company": "Transdev",
        "seat": "A45",
        "destinations": "Aveiro",
        "price": 0
    },
    "hash": "afd49088c68c2c17c329aedd6fbbe53a4d16b0ee8f187",
    "status": "inactive"
}     Field  Meaning  Type      ticket_id  Ticket id number  Integer    timestamp  Timestamp for when the ticket was created  Date    details  Aditional information about the ticket  Object    hash  Hash to check ticket integraty  String    status  Specifies if the ticket is disabled, validated or expired  String

Content-type: application/json  {   
  "secret": "secret",
  "ticket": {
    "ticket_id": 0,
    "timestamp": "2019-10-14T10:03:57.756Z",
    "details": {
      "purpose": "Transportation ticket",
      "company": "Transdev",
      "seat": "A45",
      "destinations": "Aveiro",
      "price": 0
    },
    "hash": "afd49088c68c2c17c329aedd6fbbe53a4d16b0ee8f187",
    "status": "inactive"
  }
}     Field  Meaning  Type      secret  Value to use when creating the hash  String    ticket  Ticket to be validated  Object

When validating a ticket, there are 2 different successful responses. When the ticket's status is inactive the response body contains an updated instance of the ticket with a new status value and hash.  Content-type: application/json  {
    "ticket_id": 0,
    "timestamp": "2019-10-14T10:04:30.666Z",
    "details": {
      "purpose": "Transportation ticket",
      "company": "Transdev",
      "seat": "A45",
      "destinations": "Aveiro",
      "price": 0
    },
    "hash": "afd49088c68c2c17c329aedd6fbbe53a4d16b0ee8f187",
    "status": "validated"
}     Field  Meaning  Type      ticket_id  Ticket id number  Integer    user_id  User id number  Integer    timestamp  Timestamp for when the ticket was created  Date    details  Aditional information about the ticket  Object    hash  Hash to check ticket integraty  String    status  Specifies if the ticket is inactive, validated or expired  String     When the ticket's status is validated an ok is returned.     Error  Meaning      200  Ticket has been validated successfully.    201  Ticket is currently valid.     If the ticket can't be validated an error is returned.     Error  Meaning      404  Invalid ticket    405  Ticket has expired
